<p> 
An abstract class is one which cannot be instantiated, but rather serves as a template for subclasses 
to inherit from.  The keyword <tt>abstract</tt> is used to declare a class as abstract.
</p>

<p>
An abstract class can contain instance variables and methods like a non-abstract class, but can also contain 
<A href="glossary.php?term=abstract_method">abstract methods</A>, which will need to be <A href="glossary.php?term=overriding">overridden</A> in its subclasses.
</p>
